results.name: a(n) = min(d(n), d(A225546(n))), where d gives the number of divisors of n, A000005.
comment: This is not equal to A000005(A331288(n)). The first difference is at n=100, where a(100) = 6, while A000005(A331288(100)) = 9. Note that A225546(100) = 243 and d(243) = 6 < d(100) = 9.
link: Antti Karttunen, Table of n, a(n) for n = 1..65537
